children.subject:
I've taken 100, 170 and 188 out of these.

Winter break prep:

CS170: I would suggest just getting the 170 textbook and read through it a few passes (coarse to fine), you'd be surprised to learn different things each time you read through it. Tbh this itself is enough work over the winter break.

DS100: I think you can save this for the semester.

CS161: I would suggest reviewing related concepts from 61C. 

CS188: For 188 I would also suggest holding this off for the semester. The concepts aren't too hard but the tests are extremely difficult. I think prepping for 170 will indirectly help for 188. 

Advice for the semester:

It is more or less just pacing yourself taking these 4 techs and being able to keep up with the work throughout the semester. I always regret not learning 100% from the materials the week they are covered and having to wait until exam season to make them up. 

Good luck.

I would highly recommend you don't do this. If you haven't taken 4 techs before, you're gonna hate life half way through. 

I took 170 and 188 this semester. 170, read the textbook pretty thoroughly and try some practice exams. The concepts take a while to sink in, but once you understand them, you should be able to do fine on the exams. CS188 exams are actually so so difficult. I'm not really a math-y person, but 188 exams end up being pretty math-y and theoretical, so I would also recommend review the material ahead of time and try some practice exams to feel out the material.
do you need 53 for data 100? if so, why?
You don’t NEED it per say but it helps. The only thing helpful concept from 53 was gradient descent(partial derivatives). But that you could learn that in a weekend.

Watch out for when you get hit with 4 midterms in a week 😦

Stay on the of the work. Data 100 should be a breeze if you’ve taken a probability course and math 53. It’ll be comparably easy to 170 and 161. 170’s textbook is very thorough in the explanation so that would be the best bet. Haven’t taken 161 or 188 but this semester was in 170, data 100, cs186 and ieor 185. Weekly workload was manageable but when midterms come, they seriously landed all on the same week so pace yourself and really be aware to not burn out(I lost count of the number of times I stayed up and stayed over night at Moffit this semester but it’s over 15).
